Git Setup for Your Pension System Project
What Files to Push to GitHub
✅ YES - Push These Files:

frontend/ - Your entire React frontend
packages/contracts/src/ - Your smart contracts
packages/contracts/test/ - Your test files
packages/contracts/script/ - Your deployment scripts
packages/contracts/foundry.toml - Configuration
packages/contracts/foundry.lock - Dependency lock file
packages/contracts/README.md - Documentation
packages/contracts/.gitignore - Git ignore rules

❌ NO - Don't Push These (Add to .gitignore):

packages/contracts/lib/ - Dependencies (too large, can be reinstalled)
packages/contracts/out/ - Compiled contracts (generated files)
packages/contracts/cache/ - Build cache
node_modules/ - Frontend dependencies
.env files - Environment variables

Step 1: Create .gitignore Files
